<subSubSection id="C329E09709064652FF5ACA75FCAE2726" box="[197,841,834,859]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C09064652FF5ACA75FCAE2726" blockId="12.[151,1436,258,966]" box="[197,841,834,859]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E09064652FF5ACA75FEAC2727" bold="true" box="[197,331,835,859]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is descriptive for the robust styles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329E09709064652FF5ACA51FE5C27BA" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8CB31C09064652FF5ACA51FE5C27BA" blockId="12.[151,1436,258,966]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E09064652FF5ACA51FEDE2703" bold="true" box="[197,313,871,895]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has similar genitalia features to 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F09064652FCD3CA51FC372702" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[844,976,870,894]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bolidiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E09064652FCD3CA51FC372702" box="[844,976,870,894]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">B. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be separated by the very long, robust style with subapical spines (
<figureCitation id="1308AF9909064652FD80CABCFD4127DE" box="[543,678,906,930]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[237,1341,203,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-62@13.[221,1354,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov. (25) pygofer, lateral view; (26) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (27) right style, lateral view; (28) right style, dorsal view; (29) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (30) aedeagus, ventral view; (31) connective, dorsal view." pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Figs. 27, 28</figureCitation>
) and absence of a long curved spine on the aedeagus that is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C33C89F09064652FF2BCA98FEF127BA" authorityName="Nielson" authorityYear="2011" box="[180,278,942,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bolidiana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B9476F0E09064652FF2BCA98FEF127BA" box="[180,278,942,966]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figs. 44, 45).
</paragraph>
